The seminars consist in readings from all three main branches of semiotics: semiotics of culture, social semiotics, and biosemiotics. This is conducted on the basis of original texts and their close reading, and the purpose of the course is to both understand semiotics as a general science, and to learn how to associate ideas and concepts from texts from different fields.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to read and analyse the basic texts of semiotics: the classics which have inspired and been the basis for semiotics and its development in general. The seminars provide basic knowledge about semiotics on the basis of original texts, and teach close reading and the analysis of texts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Acquiring foundational knowledge, and learning close reading and skills of associating ideas.
